Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
Mallory Green is a 178,000 square foot Class A office Building designed for the modern worker. Surrounded by green space, walking trails, and unparalleled access Mallory Green is a perfect fit for today's corporate user. The property was the first office building in Tennessee to be Wired Certified offering superior connectivity. Natural light is abounding with floor to ceiling glass windows.

Mallory Green is located off of the McEwen/I65 interchange on Mallory Lane. It is surrounded by over 40 restaurants which makes grabbing lunch that much easier.

Common.Highlight.Common.Text: Executive suites and open plan work stations

Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text:
308 Mallory Station Rd is located in Nashville’s popular Cool Springs submarket. This submarket sits in Williamson County, a state leader in both job and population growth. With 13 out of the 25 largest companies in Nashville located in Williamson County, the market’s economy is thriving.
Williamson County boasts a low unemployment rate and a highly educated workforce. That, along with a relatively low cost of living and highly rated school system, further amplifies area’s appeal. With a median household income of $106,045 and a median home value of $472,000, Williamson County has attracted a vibrant community that takes advantage of proximity to top employers, great schools, and plentiful amenities.

Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text: Just twenty miles from Nashville, Franklin has anchored it’s development in a unique heritage that honors its charming character while progressively becoming a leader in statewide population and job growth. Alongside Franklin’s economic and business development has been the growth of a sought after lifestyle community, providing business owners with a progressive and thriving demographic.
